ruby-hoe
------------------------------------------
Hoe is a simple rake/rubygems helper for project Rakefiles. It generates 
all the usual tasks for projects including rdoc generation, testing, 
packaging, and deployment.

Runtime requirements:
  rake-0.7.2-1
  ruby-1.8.6_p114-2
  ruby-rubyforge-0.4.5-1
  rubygems-1.2.0-1

Canonical website:
  http://seattlerb.rubyforge.org/hoe/

Canonical download:
  http://rubyforge.org/projects/seattlerb/files

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack ruby-hoe-1.7.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./ruby-hoe-1.7.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ruby-hoe-1.7.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/ruby-hoe-1.7.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/bin/sow
  /usr/lib/ruby/site_ruby/1.8/hoe.rb
  /usr/share/doc/ruby-hoe-1.7.0/HISTORY.txt
  /usr/share/doc/ruby-hoe-1.7.0/README.txt

------------------

